com.serena.dmclient.api
Interface Project

All Superinterfaces:
DimensionsArObject, DimensionsLcObject, DimensionsObject
public interface Project
extends DimensionsLcObject

Represent a Dimensions project (was workset) with optional attribute values and relationships populated into its cache.

importItems

DimensionsResult importItems(java.util.List itemsToImport)
Imports the specified items into this project.

It is important to note that the items to be imported must exist in the current project for this operation to succeed.

Parameters:
itemsToImport - a list of either ItemRevision objects or ItemRevision objects that must be imported
Returns:
the result of the operation, as reported by the server
Throws:
java.lang.NullPointerException - if itemsToImport is null
java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if itemsToImport.size() == 0 or if the list contains anything other than ItemRevision or ItemRevision objects
DimensionsRuntimeException - if the specified items do not exist in the current project

upload

java.util.List upload(java.util.List files,
                      java.lang.String relativeLocation,
                      boolean forceBranch,
                      boolean forceTip,
                      boolean forceCheckin,
                      java.lang.String comment,
                      java.lang.String description,
                      boolean keep,
                      java.lang.String attributes,
                      java.lang.String codePage,
                      java.lang.String relatedChdocs,
                      Part part,
                      java.lang.String logFile,
                      java.lang.String userDirectory,
                      java.lang.String contentEncoding,
                      boolean verbose)
Runs the Upload command in a non-executing modus. Returns information for each item like Status, Command to execute, etc. which then can be passed on to the user or executed directly.

Parameters:
files - List of FileToUpload objects that should be uploaded (the list can be obtained by FileToUpload.scanDirectory)
relativeLocation - An offset in the workset. E.g. uploading c:\workspace\projfoo\junit\awtui\AboutDialog.java, which has workset path bar/yuk/acme/junit/awtui/AboutDialog.java requires specifying the files in the files list parameter in the form c:\workspace\projfoo\junit\awtui\AboutDialog.java, the userDirectory parameter in the form c:\workspace\projfoo\ and the relativeLocation parameter in the form bar\yuk\acme (Pass in an empty string if no offset is required.)
forceBranch - forces a new revision created as branch
forceTip - forces a new revision created as tip (mutually exclusive with option forceBranch
forceCheckin - forces an update for items without metadata
comment - Comment for new item revisions to be created
description - Description for new items to be created
keep - Whether the copy of the item should stay untouched or be deleted
attributes - String of attribute values for all items in the list (in the form: attrName="attrValue",attrName2="attrValue2",)
codePage - Name of the codepage to be used. If not supplied, standard codepage is used.
relatedChdocs - String of requests to be related (in the form: "PAYROLL_CR_1", "PAYROLL_CR_2")
part - Part new Items should be related to. If not suppplied, root part is used.
logFile - Path of log file for output xml file. If not supplied, temporary file is used and deleted
userDirectory - Directory that is used as the root directory for comparing
contentEncoding - Specifies the content encoding for the new revision to be created. If not supplied, standard encoding is used. See TextEncodings.java for possible values.
verbose - Verbose output
Returns:
List List of FileToUpload objects containing the result for each passed in item.

download

java.util.List download(java.lang.String projectDirectory,
                        java.lang.String userDirectory,
                        java.lang.String codePage,
                        java.lang.String logFile,
                        boolean recursive,
                        boolean touch,
                        boolean expand,
                        boolean overwrite,
                        boolean checkConflict)
Runs the Download command in a non-executing modus. Returns information for each item like Status, Command to execute, etc. which then can be passed on to the user or executed directly.

Parameters:
projectDirectory - The directory in the project that should be downloaded (Pass in empty string if root directory should be taken)
userDirectory - the directory in the user area that the project should be compared to
codePage - Name of the codepage to be used. If not supplied, standard codepage is used.
logFile - Path of log file for output xml file. If not supplied, temporary file is used and deleted
recursive - Whether all subdirectories of the project should be downloaded as well
touch - Whether the files should get the current timestamp (true) or the timestamp stored in the database (false)
expand - Whether the substitution variables should get expanded when fetching the items
overwrite - Whether locally changed files should be overwritten
checkConflict - Whether download should check for conflicts for each item revision to be fetched. If any unresolved conflicts are found, Dimensions issues a warning and ignores the corresponding revision.
Returns:
List List of FileToUpload objects containing the results

Build project.

Parameters:

buildClean - area is to be cleaned of targets before the build process begins.

populate - download files to work area before each build.
traverseRequests - traverse child source requests.

                                  java.util.List items,
                                  Request request,
                                  boolean traverseRequests,
                                  boolean includeAll)
Deprecated. use getImpactedTargetsEx instead

Gets a list impacted build targets as a List of BuildTargetDetails instances. Normally you pass only one of either items or request, and pass includeAll as false.

Parameters:
buildConfigurationName - build configuration.
items - List of ItemRevision instances whose impacted targets will be queried, or null to query impacted targets for the whole project.

traverseRequests - traverse child source requests of request.
includeAll - include all targets.
Returns:
a list of BuildTargetDetails objects.

syncQueryItemInfo

com.serena.dmfile.ItemMetadata[] syncQueryItemInfo(com.serena.dmfile.ItemMetadata[] localMetadatas,
                                                   com.serena.dmfile.ItemMetadata[] remoteMetadatas)
Query for a list of metadata for common ancestors. In result list we should have the following : if result uid == PCMS_INVALID_UID, there is no common ancestor (it's a different item, or no query requested) if result uid == local uid then workset is derived from local if result uid == remote uid then local file revision is derived from workset else result uid would be common ancestor UID The result array would have the following item statuses 0 - item revision no longer exists in repository 1 - item revision exists but not in workset 2 - item revision exists and is in the workset

Parameters:
localMetadatas -
remoteMetadatas -
Returns:
list of metadatas for common ancestors - see details above.
